Package: iMDH
Type: Package
Title: Incremental estimation of minimum density hyperplanes for clustering
Version: 0.1.0
Author: David P. Hofmeyr
Maintainer: David P. Hofmeyr <dhofmeyr@sun.ac.za>
Description: Uses stochastic gradient descent to estimate low density separators for clustering. These are combined in a
 divisive hierarchical model to obtain a complete clustering solution. A pruning refinement based on in-cluster sum-of-squares
 is used to obtain a final model, and an appropriate number of clusters can be chosen automatically or manually.
License: GPL
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: Rcpp (>= 0.12.16)
LinkingTo: Rcpp, RcppArmadillo
LazyData: true
